Name: Description
Employment Population Ratio: The employment population ratio represents the proportion of the population aged 16 and over that are currently employed.

Name: Source Notes
Employment Population Ratio: U.S. Census Bureau, American Community Survey 1-Year Estimates, Table S2301 (2005-2019, 2021-2022); retrieved from https://data.census.gov/.

Name: Notes
Employment Population Ratio:
Please note, we do not report 2020 American Community Survey 1-year estimates. Due to disruptions and biases in data collection during 2020, the Census Bureau released the “experimental” 1-year estimates for 2020 and advises against comparing against estimates from prior or future years.

Previously, CCC calculated the employment population ratio for the working age population (aged 16 to 64). In December 2019, CCC adjusted this indicator to measure the employment population ratio of the civilian population aged 16 and older, in line with reporting from the Bureau of Labor Statistics.
